        <descriptionSet>
            <description>Antonio Pini-Corsi, an operatic baritone then singing with the Metropolitan Opera, sent this postcard to his tenor friend in 1900. The card shows the Masonic Temple in Chicago, with a hand drawn musical score along the bottom.  This Travel and Landmark postcard shows how senders personalized these mass-produced objects.  Over 1 billion postcards were sold annually between 1900 and 1915, the height of the postcard craze.</description>
